{"scriptures":{"scriptures":[{"chapter":21,"paragraph":125,"verse":1,"section_id":30,"block":null,"verse_id":1021001,"content":"The <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> <crossref let=\"k\" cid=\"c01021001.1\"/>visited Sarah as he had said, and the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> did to Sarah <crossref let=\"l\" cid=\"c01021001.2\"/>as he had promised.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Birth of Isaac"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":125,"verse":2,"section_id":30,"block":null,"verse_id":1021002,"content":"And Sarah <crossref let=\"m\" cid=\"c01021002.1\"/>conceived and bore Abraham a son in his old age <crossref let=\"n\" cid=\"c01021002.2\"/>at the time of which God had spoken to him.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Birth of Isaac"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":125,"verse":3,"section_id":30,"block":null,"verse_id":1021003,"content":"Abraham called the name of his son who was born to him, whom Sarah bore him, <crossref let=\"o\" cid=\"c01021003.1\"/>Isaac. <footnote><i class=\"catch-word\">Isaac</i> means <i>he laughs</i></footnote>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Birth of Isaac"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":125,"verse":4,"section_id":30,"block":null,"verse_id":1021004,"content":"And Abraham <crossref let=\"p\" cid=\"c01021004.1\"/>circumcised his son Isaac when he was eight days old, <crossref let=\"q\" cid=\"c01021004.2\"/>as God had commanded him.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Birth of Isaac"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":125,"verse":5,"section_id":30,"block":null,"verse_id":1021005,"content":"<crossref let=\"r\" cid=\"c01021005.1\"/>Abraham was a hundred years old when his son Isaac was born to him.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Birth of Isaac"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":125,"verse":6,"section_id":30,"block":null,"verse_id":1021006,"content":"And Sarah said, <crossref let=\"s\" cid=\"c01021006.1\"/>\"God has made laughter for me; everyone who hears will laugh over me. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Birth of Isaac"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":125,"verse":7,"section_id":30,"block":null,"verse_id":1021007,"content":"And she said, \"Who would have said to Abraham that Sarah would nurse children? <crossref let=\"t\" cid=\"c01021007.1\"/>Yet I have borne him a son in his old age. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Birth of Isaac"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":126,"verse":8,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021008,"content":"And the child grew and was weaned. And Abraham made a great feast on the day that Isaac was weaned.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":126,"verse":9,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021009,"content":"But Sarah <crossref let=\"u\" cid=\"c01021009.1\"/>saw the son of Hagar the Egyptian, whom she had borne to Abraham, <crossref let=\"v\" cid=\"c01021009.2\"/>laughing. <footnote>Possibly <i><span class=\"catch-word\">laughing</span> in mockery</i></footnote>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":126,"verse":10,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021010,"content":"So she said to Abraham, <crossref let=\"w\" cid=\"c01021010.1\"/>\"Cast out this slave woman with her son, for the son of this slave woman shall not be heir with my son Isaac. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":126,"verse":11,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021011,"content":"And the thing was very displeasing to Abraham on account of his son.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":126,"verse":12,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021012,"content":"But God said to Abraham, \"Be not displeased because of the boy and because of your slave woman. Whatever Sarah says to you, do as she tells you, for <crossref let=\"x\" cid=\"c01021012.1\"/>through Isaac shall your offspring be named.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":126,"verse":13,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021013,"content":"And I will make <crossref let=\"y\" cid=\"c01021013.1\"/>a nation of the son of the slave woman also, because he is your offspring. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":126,"verse":14,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021014,"content":"So Abraham rose early in the morning and took bread and a skin of water and gave it to Hagar, putting it on her shoulder, along with the child, and sent her away. And she departed and wandered in the wilderness of <crossref let=\"z\" cid=\"c01021014.1\"/>Beersheba.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":127,"verse":15,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021015,"content":"When the water in the skin was gone, she put the child under one of the bushes.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":127,"verse":16,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021016,"content":"Then she went and sat down opposite him a good way off, about the distance of a bowshot, for she said, \"Let me not look on the death of the child. \" And as she sat opposite him, she lifted up her voice and wept.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":127,"verse":17,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021017,"content":"And God heard the voice of the boy, and the angel of God called to Hagar from heaven and said to her, \"What troubles you, Hagar? Fear not, for God has heard the voice of the boy where he is.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":127,"verse":18,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021018,"content":"Up! Lift up the boy, and hold him fast with your hand, for I will make him into a great nation. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":127,"verse":19,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021019,"content":"Then <crossref let=\"a\" cid=\"c01021019.1\"/>God opened her eyes, and she saw a well of water. And she went and filled the skin with water and gave the boy a drink.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":127,"verse":20,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021020,"content":"And God was with the boy, and he grew up. He lived in the wilderness <crossref let=\"b\" cid=\"c01021020.1\"/>and became an expert with the bow.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":127,"verse":21,"section_id":31,"block":null,"verse_id":1021021,"content":"He lived in the wilderness of Paran, and his mother took a wife for him from the land of Egypt.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God Protects Hagar and Ishmael"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":128,"verse":22,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021022,"content":"At that time <crossref let=\"c\" cid=\"c01021022.1\"/>Abimelech and Phicol the commander of his army said to Abraham, <crossref let=\"d\" cid=\"c01021022.2\"/>\"God is with you in all that you do.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":128,"verse":23,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021023,"content":"Now therefore swear to me here by God that you will not deal falsely with me or with my descendants or with my posterity, but <crossref let=\"e\" cid=\"c01021023.1\"/>as I have dealt kindly with you, so you will deal with me and with the land where you have sojourned. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":128,"verse":24,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021024,"content":"And Abraham said, \"I will swear. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":25,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021025,"content":"When Abraham reproved Abimelech about a well of water that Abimelech's servants <crossref let=\"f\" cid=\"c01021025.1\"/>had seized,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":26,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021026,"content":"Abimelech said, \"I do not know who has done this thing; you did not tell me, and I have not heard of it until today. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":27,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021027,"content":"So Abraham took sheep and oxen and gave them to Abimelech, and the two men <crossref let=\"g\" cid=\"c01021027.1\"/>made a covenant.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":28,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021028,"content":"Abraham set seven ewe lambs of the flock apart.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":29,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021029,"content":"And Abimelech said to Abraham, \"What is the meaning of these seven ewe lambs that you have set apart?\"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":30,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021030,"content":"He said, \"These seven ewe lambs you will take from my hand, that this<footnote>Or <i>you</i></footnote> may be a witness for me that I dug this well. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":31,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021031,"content":"Therefore <crossref let=\"h\" cid=\"c01021031.1\"/>that place was called Beersheba,<footnote><i class=\"catch-word\">Beersheba</i> means <i>well of seven</i> or <i>well of the oath</i></footnote> because there both of them swore an oath.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":32,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021032,"content":"So they made a covenant at Beersheba. Then Abimelech and Phicol the commander of his army rose up and returned to the land of the Philistines.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":33,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021033,"content":"Abraham planted a tamarisk tree in Beersheba and <crossref let=\"i\" cid=\"c01021033.1\"/>called there on the name of the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span>, <crossref let=\"j\" cid=\"c01021033.2\"/>the Everlasting God.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"},{"chapter":21,"paragraph":129,"verse":34,"section_id":32,"block":null,"verse_id":1021034,"content":"And Abraham sojourned many days in the land of the Philistines. <end-chapter/>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"A Treaty with Abimelech"}],"x_refs":{"c01021001.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"1 Sam. 2:21","start_ref_id":9002021,"verse_id":1021001,"letter_id":"k"}],"c01021012.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Rom. 9:7","start_ref_id":45009007,"verse_id":1021012,"letter_id":"x"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Heb. 11:18","start_ref_id":58011018,"verse_id":1021012,"letter_id":"x"}],"c01021001.2":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"17:19","start_ref_id":1017019,"verse_id":1021001,"letter_id":"l"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"18:10","start_ref_id":1018010,"verse_id":1021001,"letter_id":"l"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"14","start_ref_id":1018014,"verse_id":1021001,"letter_id":"l"}],"c01021002.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Heb. 11:11","start_ref_id":58011011,"verse_id":1021002,"letter_id":"m"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Gal. 4:22","start_ref_id":48004022,"verse_id":1021002,"letter_id":"m"}],"c01021013.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"18","start_ref_id":1021018,"verse_id":1021013,"letter_id":"y"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"16:10","start_ref_id":1016010,"verse_id":1021013,"letter_id":"y"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_ti